-- Europe's Van Rompuy confident of a deal on Greece
-- 
-- Fri Jun 17, 2011 11:15am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2011/06/17/us-ireland-europe-vanrompuy-idUSTRE75G3SH20110617

 

 DUBLIN  (Reuters) - The president of the European Council said on Friday he was confident a fresh bailout deal for Greece would be hammered. 

 In a speech during an official one-day visit to Dublin Herman Van Rompuy urged Greece's politicians to agreed to a package of austerity measures crucial to unlocking its financial predicament. "This is no time for party politics, there is too much at stake," Van Rompuy said. (Reporting by Carmel Crimmins)